  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7045.72 sitting just below the massive 7050 gamma wall (13.3B), dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push above this level as they hedge their long gamma exposure in the PIN regime. The proximity to max positive gamma at 7050 creates a strong magnetic effect, with dealers providing natural resistance on rallies and support on dips toward the 7030 level (6.1B GEX). Key levels to watch are the 7050 resistance wall above and 7015 negative gamma pocket below where dealer buying would accelerate any breakdown.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get pinned around 7050 with limited upside until this gamma wall is cleared.",
